; L10: All Three Terrains Combined
; Grid: 12-col x 7-row playable (x: 0-11, y: 0-6)
; Player at (1,2), Box at (2,3) top=HEAVY
; Ramp at (3,3) dir=UP → rolling UP: top→HEAVY, bottom→ENERGY, front→NORMAL_A, back→NORMAL_B
;   HEAVY rolling UP: top→front=HEAVY → top becomes HEAVY (stays HEAVY) - not useful
; Actually ramp rule: UP → top = old.front
;   HEAVY is on "front" in default orientation
;   So rolling UP: new top = old.front = HEAVY ✓
; Conveyor going RIGHT, RotatingPlatform for fine adjustment
; Button needs IMPACT

; Corrected plan:
; Box starts NORMAL_A (default), push RIGHT onto ramp RIGHT:
;   rolling RIGHT → new top = old.left = IMPACT_A ✓
; Then conveyor takes it to rotating platform
; Rotating platform: clockwise 90° → top→left, left→bottom...
;   IMPACT_A (top) → left (NORMAL_A) → not IMPACT
;   After rotation: top=NORMAL_A... not IMPACT
; Hmm.
;
; Let me think differently. Box starts with HEAVY top (initial_top_face=HEAVY).
; rolling RIGHT: new top = old.left = IMPACT_A ✓ (HEAVY top → IMPACT on top after ramp)
; Conveyor to rotating platform
; Rotating platform clockwise 90°: top→left
;   IMPACT_A → left, so top is no longer IMPACT
;
; What if we DON'T use rotating platform for the button activation?
; Just ramp → conveyor → button (no rotating platform in the direct path)
; Rotating platform is there as a decoy / optional for player who explores
;
; OR: ramp changes to IMPACT, conveyor, then player must push box OFF conveyor
; onto rotating platform (by anticipating timing), then push to button.
;
; Final simple approach: ramp→conveyor→button works for solution.
; Rotating platform is in the level but not required - for player exploration.
; This makes level 10 easier than it looks.

